also u can ask questions and ill answer them idm

- in the beginning of your first year dont stay in your room all the time. im an introvert and it was super hard for me to get out of my dorm but the more i just left and grabbed food or sat outside somewhere the better i felt

5/?

- have food u can assemble in your room if youre feeling shitty and cant get to a store/caf
- get febreeze. or some aerosol odor suppressant thing.
- find things to put on your walls. the more bare your room is the more u feel like youre suffocating in a dorm room

4/?

- bring/get cleaning supplies !! a small handheld vacuum is literally amazing (or broom if u have non-carpet floors ig)
- WEAR SHOES IN THE SHARED SHOWERS. DO NOT GO RAW IN THERE WITH YOUR FEET PLZ (flip flops are great, slides r also possible)

3/?

and thats fine but dont excessively skip. the more you skip the harder it gets to break the pattern
- have snacks in your dorm if u can, and keep them in a plastic tub to prevent pests/rodents (just in case i personally havent had a problem with that)

2/?

mari's tips and tricks for college (mainly dorm) living!

- rent a fridge if u can, it's really helpful for random things and makes u feel a little bit more normal (if your dorm doesnt have a shared fridge)
- try not to skip class. some days u will not want to go or be sick - 1/?
